    "liarGameData": {
        "trap": "듣는 사람이 화자의 할아버지라면, 화자는 자신의 아버지에 대해 말할 때 항상 높임말을 써야 한다.",
        "correctVersion": "한국의 압존법(Honorific shift)에 따르면, 듣는 사람이 말의 대상보다 높은 서열일 경우 말의 대상에 대한 높임말을 생략하거나 낮추어야 한다.",
        "explanation": "Abjon-beop (압존법) is a specific Korean etiquette rule regarding honorifics in front of a third party. The trap suggests you should ALWAYS use honorifics for your father, regardless of the listener. However, if you are speaking to your grandfather (who is higher in rank than your father), you should actually drop the honorifics for your father to show more respect to your grandfather. For example, instead of '아버지가 오셨습니다' (Father has come), you would say '아버지가 왔습니다' or '아버지가 들어왔습니다' when speaking to the grandfather. This hierarchy-based shift is a subtle but important part of K-Etiquette."
    }
}